ce Verant is bringing the axe to any guilds with less than 10 members.  Anywhich way, though the guild was originally built on the alliance of 3 guilds that folded, I will most likely be restructuring it to fit a smaller membership of mostly people I have either played with for around a year, or know in RL so I am sure of the character of the people behind the characters ;) so to speak.   So on that note, just wanted to let you know if you see the Dark Phoenix tag displayed attack on sight.. for our members will fight fair as far as OOC stuff goes, and with pure hate in char (of course).  Not sure how the shanks have been leveling, but our members will mostly be mid teens/twenties/low thirties.  so if anyone cares to set up 'player quests' via missions, ambushes, field battles.. drop me a line via my email.<br>
...Also, another thing.  I recently had a bout with one of the guild memembers of "Global Menance".. well, a couple of them.  One was completely rude and childish OOC to me, but then later, when I sought my vengance for his slight in game against another of his guild.. we (the second guy, whom I killed) ended up in a length conversation ooc, that was quiet polite.  He apologized for the other members behavoir, and went on to say that there guild was atually purist like the Shanks, and even had alliance with thee.  I'm just curious to confirm this, so I know to add there guild to my list of PvP enemies worth bothering with/showing ooc respect to.<br>
--well, if any of this is confusing, contribute it to lack of sleep and working 11 hours 3rd shift ;)  thanks for having me in, I'll stop by to see the reaction.  Not all of my chars are pure evil, although.. the Dark Phoenix for all purposes will be ;)<br>
 <p><table><tr><td><img src=http://www.geocities.com/draconica369/Storage/defsymbol.gif></td><td>Lady Savia'nie<br>Teir'dal Ul'Veldriss<br>Realm of Valon'Zek</td><tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a8a8a8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umajestykvz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MajestykVZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Council of Elders</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/16/00 8:07:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ftheshanksgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Allies'n Enemies</span><hr size=1> /ooc<br>
<br>
Savia,<br>
<br>
We welcome the challenge and the fun of new PvP/RP dark guild.  I don't beleive that any of us in the Shanks like the "Quake" type of PvP, where any and all methods are used to defeat another, then insult them /ooc afterwards.  Neither, do we whine, when we've been beaten.<br>
<br>
We have an alliance with any Guild that is human team only, 4v4 team PvP, and follows the same rules of conduct that we do.  The Global Menace, has done so on every occasion that we have fought together.<br>
<br>
Some of the GM do have a tendancy to "smack talk" /ooc a bit.  Usually I've seen this in response to another's antogonistic /ooc remarks.  Most though are honorable characters and suffer only from the bad rep given to them by the same characters that try to give it to us.<br>
<br>
Good luck with the guild restructuring.  I look forward to seeing you before you see me soon. ;) <p>Majestyk, <a href="http://Server3.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse">Rogue</a>, Leader, <a href="http://galaxy.apropos.org/shanks">Shanks</a>, <a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/board.asp?brd=5034">Vallon Zek!</a>

We as Shanks, have chosen the hard path. In the hardness of it, is where we find the glory.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/unorlalos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norlalos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Patron</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/16/00 1:00:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ftheshanksgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Allies'n Enemies</span><hr size=1> Savia,<br>
<br>
I believe It was me that you talked to in the lenghty OOC conversation. I remember you killing me as I was &quot;sleeping&quot; on the hill in Misty.<br>
<br>
Heh, was a good converstaion, I thought, and am glad that you viewed me as polite. I try. Anyway, just thought I'd say &quot; Hello &quot; to you here, since I frequent this local.<br>
<br>
Until next time we meet. Take care, and safe travels.<br>
