well, I had begun working on reforging Dark Phoenix but never finished. about mid way through revamping the message board ect, I started talking with an old guild ally from House V'Umbra and decided on a different course of action.  I joined my primary to there house as officer in her position, and represenative of a guild alliance (in char). OOC, we just merged basically.  I brought in all my 'agents' that I had dispersed through various guilds, and decided it would be easier to let another hold full leadership so I can work on my own projects so to speak.  <br>
--House V'Umbra is roleplay only, and dark team only as well, so if you encounter them you can expect a good enemy to fight against.  Although, the guild is hardly PvP oriented.  Over time I will attempt to push for more PvP though, perhaps down the road we can ooc set up some kind of guild vs guild zone war.  I think that would be a blast :)  I love fighting against someone I know doesent take it personally out of char.  At one point, I thought about making a guild where it was both light and dark team, but where both sides warred with each other constantly.  RHT already does that though, so thats not much of a new idea at this point.  ok, well I gotta run, take care all ye shankers;) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uceescrit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ceescrit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Patron</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/2/00 8:58:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ftheshanksgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hi'ya again, been awhile since I checked up </span><hr size=1> &lt;Stumbles into a barbarian infested Mead hall&gt;<br>
